tors suppliers unions governments and trade bodies understand our objectives plans and results and how our activities and businesses contribute to the wider community  operating in a nonhierarchical environment we have flat and flexible teams because we believe that to create value everyone’s contribution should be sought directly and their opinions and ideas considered without being filtered we like the challenge and rigour this brings to the decisionmaking process there are no contrived limitations on how quickly individuals can progress through the organisation terra firma gives people the opportunity to develop their roles as quickly as their ability allows william burnard legal counsel ishan bharadwaj associate director whenever you find yourself on the side of the majority it is time to pause and reflect henry miller transforming businesses delivering value   all rights reserved terra firma capital partners limited site map disclaimer privacy statement guy hands print this page bookmark this page email this page accept our website uses cookies by continuing to use this website you have consented to have cookies placed on your computer to find out more please refer to our privacy statement private equity  terra firma investor login choose language  english   search skip navigation home about us about us about private equity a global outlook our approach our history our culture portfolio portfolio current investments historical investments focus terra firma investment strategy transformational private equity operational real estate renewable energy infrastructure people people terra firma senior team employee training and development careers operating partners  senior advisers fund general partners investors investors alignment of interest funds investor relations team form  responsibility responsibility environmental social governance transparency communications communications news media coverage guy hands’ view letters and speeches from guy hands annual reviews an alternative perspective contacts contact   skip navigation about us about private equity a global outlook our approach investment strategy creating value transforming businesses our history our culture   about private equity private equity aims to create longterm value by transforming businesses away from the public markets as a private equity investment firm we typically raise private equity funds from large institutional investors such as pension funds financial institutions sovereign wealth funds endowments and family offices by investing in private equity these institutions aim to seek higher returns to improve their overall performance  the private equity funds we raise are used to acquire assetbacked businesses that can be transformed through fundamental change as a private equity firm we aim to create longterm value by transforming businesses away from the public markets we search for opportunities which have been overlooked we actively seek out investments in sectors which may be out of favour and in businesses which have been undermanaged or undercapitalised  through a combination of strategic change improved management and sustained investment we transform our private equity portfolio businesses creating value for all our stakeholders these healthier companies are subsequently sold or listed on the public stock markets to realise a return for the investors in our funds private equity has done an extraordinary job over the years of redefining and reinvigorating businesses that have experienced turbulent times and required new business models tim pryce transforming businesses delivering value   all rights reserved terra firma capital partners limited site map disclaimer privacy statement guy hands print this page bookmark this page email this page accept our website uses cookies by continuing to use this website you have consented to have cookies placed on your computer to find out more please refer to our privacy statement terra firma the private equity firm investor login choose language  english   search skip navigation home about us about us about private equity a global outlook our approach our history our culture portfolio portfolio current investments historical investments focus terra firma investment strategy transformational private equity operational real estate renewable energy infrastructure people people terra firma senior team employee training and development careers operating partners  senior advisers fund general partners investors investors alignment of interest funds investor relations team form  responsibility responsibility environmental social governance transparency communications communications news media coverage guy hands’ view letters and speeches from guy hands annual reviews an alternative perspective contacts contact   transforming businesses delivering value our firm terra firma is one of europe’s leading private equity firms we create value for our stakeholders by acquiring transforming and selling assetbacked businesses we transform the strategy operations and finances of our businesses to make them bestinclass more about creating value more about terra firma our portfolio we built infinis into one of the leading independent uk renewable energy generators we created annington the largest private owner of residential property in england and wales we have developed awas into one of the worlds leading aircraft leasing companies we own cpc the largest privately owned beef producer in australia we own rtr italy’s leading solar energy business we own wyevale garden centres the largest plant and gardenfocused retailer in the uk we have built everpower into a top us wind energy development and generation company four seasons health care is the uk’s largest independent elderly and specialist care provider more about our portfolio guy hands view latest news  july  terra firma announces annington refinancing to provide long term stability through landmark transaction terra firma one of europ