rtners i – the fund comprised assets acquired between  and  and is now fully realised nomura international plc was the sole equity investor in the portfolio terra firma capital partners ii – tfcp ii was closed in february  raising a total of € billion it is currently managing investments on behalf of  investors from  countries the fund was established to follow terra firma’s strategy of making control investments in asset or cash flowrich companies in complex and often regulated sectors principally in europe terra firma capital partners iii – tfcp iii was closed in may  raising a total of € billion it is currently managing investments on behalf of  investors from  countries the fund follows the same investment strategy as tfcp ii terra firma deutsche annington – tfda was established in  and held terra firma’s german housing assets in deutsche annington immobilien group terra firma raised € billion‎ through tfda in order to buy deutsche annington along with cpi from tfcpi tfda acquired  with the balance being acquired by cpi additional capital was secured to allow deutsche annington to continue its strategy of acquiring principally german residential properties in  deutsche annington completed an ipo and began trading on the frankfurt stock exchange with a free float of  in may  with terra firma’s ownership of deutsche annington at  tfda distributed its deutsche annington shares on a pro rata basis to the tfda investors terra firma special opportunities fund i  tfsofi closed in december  and is a single asset fund raised to acquire annington homes from nomura tfsofi raised a total of £ million from investors around the world both institutional and private ryan macaskill portfolio business financial controller robbie barr senior adviser €bn current funds under management transforming businesses delivering value   all rights reserved terra firma capital partners limited site map disclaimer privacy statement guy hands print this page bookmark this page email this page a